olive oil
1 avocado
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
½ tbs honey
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet garlic aioli

• Slice avocado in half and scoop out flesh.
• In a medium bowl, mash avocado with a drizzle of olive oil and generous pinch of salt until smooth.

• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook beef mince (no need for oil!), breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add kiwi spice blend seasoning and the honey, and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Meanwhile, in a large bowl combine shredded red cabbage, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts until warmed through.

• Top each tortilla with smashed avocado, red cabbage and spiced beef.
• Drizzle over garlic aioli. Enjoy!

• If you've added a fancify bundle, dollop over roasted tomato salsa, sprinkle over shredded Cheddar cheese and tear over coriander.